snippet.title: State of Play Japan | November 11, 2025 [English Subtitles]
snippet.description:
This Tuesday, we’re bringing you a special episode of State of Play running for more than 40 minutes, focusing on games created in Japan and across Asia, alongside a few other exciting updates.

From beloved series to distinctive indie creations, the show, hosted by voice actor Yuki Kaji, will be packed with great games, interviews, and new looks at anticipated titles.

State of Play Japan airs on YouTube on November 11 at 2pm PT /  5pm ET /  11pm CEST | November 12 at 7am JST.

The Japanese PlayStation YouTube channel will feature a full Japanese-language version, while the PlayStation YouTube channel will feature the Japanese audio with English subtitles. See you then!

Regarding co-streaming and video-on-demand (VOD)

Please note that this broadcast may include copyrighted content (e.g. licensed music) that PlayStation does not control. We welcome and celebrate our amazing co-streamers and creators, but licensing agreements outside our control could interfere with co-streams or VOD archives of this broadcast. If you’re planning to save this broadcast as a VOD to create recap videos, or to repost clips or segments from the show, we advise omitting any copyrighted music.

#ps5 #ps5games

snippet.title: Gambit: Le Diable Blanc | Character Reveal | Marvel Rivals
snippet.description:
Every card he plays changes the game.

Remy LeBeau - better known as Gambit - has always been more than a charming thief. His Mutant gift lets him charge any object with explosive kinetic energy, but it's his wit and finesse that make him truly dangerous.

After the Timestream Entanglement tore apart his wedding with Rogue, Gambit struck a deal with the Grandmaster himself: steal a priceless contract from the Collector, and receive Chronovium dice that could be forged into new wedding rings.

Under the guise of an intergalactic honeymoon, Remy sets off on the ultimate heist - one that will spiral into cosmic chaos far beyond his wildest dreams.

Season 5 begins on November 14 UTC!

Deal the cards. Play the odds. Steal the show!

snippet.title: Man Vs Baby | Official Trailer | Netflix
snippet.description:
After a job looking after a high-tech mansion ended in disaster thanks to an irritating insect in Man vs Bee, Trevor Bingley (Rowan Atkinson) has left the stressful world of housesitting for the quieter life of a school caretaker. That is, until a lucrative offer to look after a luxury London penthouse over Christmas proves too tempting to resist. But on the last day of term, when no one comes to collect the Baby Jesus from the school nativity, Trevor finds himself with another undersized and very unexpected companion. With a penthouse to protect and a baby to burp, will Trevor be able to have the calm Christmas he hopes for, or will festivities descend into chaos?

snippet.description:
— Attention Viewers ⚠️
— This is a Fan-Made Concept Trailer for:
— Grand Theft Auto VI

— This video is a fan-made concept trailer, created solely for artistic and entertainment purposes.The goal behind this trailer is to showcase my creativity and storytelling skills through a concept trailer based on a unique and original idea. By combining various effects, sound design, and AI technologies, I’ve crafted a cinematic experience that reimagines familiar worlds in bold and imaginative ways. This trailer is not official and is intended to entertain, inspire, and engage with the YouTube community. Thank you for your support — now let’s dive into a world shaped by creativity and craft. 🎬✨

— In this concept trailer for Grand Theft Auto VI, the story centers on Lucia, a young criminal struggling to claw her way out of poverty until a buried truth shatters her life and reveals she is the daughter of former Vice City kingpin Tommy Vercetti, now emerging from decades in the shadows. With Jason at her side and the corrupt forces of Leonida closing in, her journey turns from survival to reclamation as blood ties pull her into a legacy built on power, betrayal, and unfinished rule. The trailer suggests that Lucia’s fight is not just against the law but against the fate of inheriting an empire forged in fire, while Tommy’s return reframes the conflict into something far larger than escape — it becomes a battle for succession in the criminal heart of Vice City.

snippet.title: So... Pixar's Toy Story 5 Trailer Is Finally Here...
snippet.description:
https://youtu.be/7JKkkCD2i4o

We've been waiting for direct visuals of this thing for a long time, and Pixar has finally released the official teaser trailer for Toy Story 5. And it looks... interesting. There's a lot of pressure on making a fifth instalment and keeping it good, and though I have hopes in some places, it's fair to say that there are some red flags in there too. But it's all about tech and iPad babies, but nothing's set in stone for quality just yet. I think I'm still up in the air. But at least it's true that Pixar's Toy Story 5 Trailer Is Here...

snippet.title: The Family Plan 2 — Official Trailer | Apple TV+
snippet.description:
Deck the halls, dodge the bad guys. The Morgans are back for The Family Plan 2, this time in Europe. Streaming November 21  https://apple.co/_TheFamilyPlan2

In “The Family Plan 2,” it’s the holiday season and Dan (Mark Wahlberg) has planned the perfect vacation for his wife Jessica (Michelle Monaghan) and their kids to celebrate overseas — until a mysterious figure from his past (Kit Harington) shows up with unfinished business. An international game of cat-and-mouse ensues as Dan and his family battle, bicker and bond their way through a series of bank heists, holiday hijinks and car chases amid scenic European terrain.

The Family Plan 2 is an Apple Original Film hailing from Skydance Media, the sequel to “The Family Plan” will be directed by Cellan Jones. David Ellison, Dana Goldberg and Don Granger will produce for Skydance, alongside Wahlberg and Stephen Levinson through Municipal Pictures. John G. Scotti will executive produce along with Cellan Jones. David Coggeshall, the writer of the first movie, has returned to pen the sequel.

snippet.title: Young Jonn  - Cash Flow (feat. Wizkid) [Official Music Video]
snippet.description:
After back-to-back hits, Young Jonn returns with “Cash Flow” featuring Wizkid — a smooth anthem about living life soft, enjoying the fruits of success, and spending with ease. Opening with the reflective line “had a hard life but I live soft,” the track captures the transition from struggle to abundance, wrapped in Young Jonn’s jiggy energy and Wizkid’s signature calm delivery.

“Cash Flow” is more than a flex — it’s a celebration of growth, freedom, and the soft life. The record leads directly into Young Jonn’s highly anticipated project, Blue Disco, marking a new chapter in his sound and story.

🔵 Stream “Cash Flow” everywhere - https://youngjonn.lnk.to/cashflow

Instagram - https://bit.ly/3IeRruq
Snapchat https://bit.ly/3JgXy2x

Listen here: 
Sooner:  https://YoungJonn.lnk.to/sooner
Jiggy Forever : https://YoungJonn.lnk.to/jiggyforever
Love Is Not Enough: https://youngjonn.lnk.to/LINEcc

About Young Jonn
John Saviours Udomboso, fondly known as Young Jonn "The Wicked Producer" is an award winning Afro-pop producer, singer/songwriter. Dubbed the Sound of the Streets, "Young Jonn" is the head huncho and musical genius behind some of the most memorable Artists that own the streets in the Street-Hop or Pop genre. With over 3 awards in some of the prestigious Awards in Nigeria, Young Jonn's sound, lyrics and beats have broken several legendary Artists on the Nigerian music scene since the mid-2000s.  Young Jonn's credits have established him as one of the most iconic producers in the last 10 years. Young Jonn signed an Artist Recording Agreement with Nigeria's foremost record label, Chocolate City with the aim to transition from being a producer to a Recording Artist. His first project Love Is Not Enough was released in the April 2022. In 2024, he released his long-awaited debut album, Jiggy Forever. The album boasts of anthems like Big Big Things, Aquafina, Sharpally, and Stronger.

Subscribe to Young Jonn's channel for all the best and latest official music videos, albums, behind the scenes, live performances and more!

Dubbed the Sound of the Streets, "Young Jonn" is the head huncho and musical genius behind some of the most memorable Artists that own the streets in the Street-Hop or Pop genre. With over 3 awards in some of the prestigious Awards in Nigeria, Young Jonn's sound, lyrics and beats have broken several legendary Artists on the Nigerian music scene since the mid-2000s.  Young Jonn's credits have established him as one of the most iconic producers in the last 10 years. Young Jonn signed an Artist Recording Agreement with Nigeria's foremost record label, Chocolate City with the aim to transition from being a producer to a Recording Artist. His first project Love Is Not Enough was released in the April 2022. In 2024, he released his long-awaited debut album, Jiggy Forever. The album boasts of anthems like Big Big Things, Aquafina, Sharpally, and Stronger.

Subscribe to Young Jonn's channel for all the best and latest official music videos, albums, behind the scenes, live performances and more!

About Creedence Clearwater Revival: 
Creedence Clearwater Revival’s 1968 self-titled debut album introduced the world to guitar-playing brothers John and Tom Fogerty, drummer Doug Clifford, and bassist Stu Cook, four young men out of El Cerrito in the San Francisco Bay Area. Though they emerged in a place and time where trippy psychedelic visions were the order of the day, CCR bucked the trends and instead tapped into a rich, traditional seam of American music that connected to blues, country, rockabilly, gospel, folk and R&B.    

During their short time together as a band (1968 – 1972), the band enjoyed an unparalleled period of creativity lead by singer, songwriter, arranger John Fogerty. They’ve sold close to 100 million records, releasing 14 Top 10 hits. They also managed to play over 150 tour dates around the world, including a headlining spot at Woodstock.

Creedence Clearwater Revival’s canon has become a part of the Great American Songbook. Fogerty penned songs like “Bad Moon Rising,” “Down on the Corner,” “Fortunate Son,” “Have You Ever Seen the Rain,” “Proud Mary,” “Born on the Bayou,” “Travelin’ Band” and “Up Around the Bend” have been ingrained into pop culture — not just as rock staples, but as classic standards.

With so many memorable songs that continue to grace our radio waves, television and movie screens, plus lyrics that still resonate today, Creedence Clearwater Revival is, truly, America’s greatest rock ’n’ roll band.
